  '<p>Open-redirect (CWE-601) defense for operator-supplied <code>?next=</code> / <code>?return_to=</code> parameters. Refuses protocol-relative URLs (<code>//attacker.com</code>), backslash variants (<code>\\\\attacker.com</code>), CRLF / control chars (header-injection vector), and <code>data:</code> / <code>javascript:</code> / <code>vbscript:</code> schemes. Same-origin paths (<code>/dashboard</code>) and fragments (<code>#x</code>) pass through; full URLs require the operator to provide <code>allowedOrigins</code> or <code>allowedHosts</code> — without an allowlist, every full URL falls back. Drop the result straight into <code>res.writeHead(302, { Location: ... })</code>.</p>',
